cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with expanding pre-trained deep networks to classify novel classes with limited examples, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also introduces a hard distillation method, which is a technique commonly used in neural network compression and optimization, suggesting that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a compact generative model, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) that deals with natural language processing and text generation.
